        "details": {
            "description": "<p>Plumes of magenta and violet light and vapor shift and writhe out of a hole in reality surrounded by the fragments of a <em>runewell</em> suspended mid-explosion.</p>",
            "disable": "<p>@Check[arcana|dc:37] (master) or @Check[occultism|dc:40] (master) to redirect the magic back in on itself and cancel out the danger, or @Check[crafting|dc:40] (legendary) to reposition <em>runewell</em> fragments so they're not dangerous; three total successes are required to disable the shattered <em>runewell</em></p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 13
            },
            "publication": {
                "license": "ORC",
                "remaster": true,
                "title": "Pathfinder #219: Lord of the Trinity Star"
            },
            "reset": "",
            "routine": "<p>(3 actions) When the shattered runewell takes its first action, a towering, 30-foot-tall image of Runelord Xanderghul formed from scintillating magenta and violet light and fire looms up from the runewell. On each of the hazard's three actions, this manifestation of Runelord Xanderghul scowls down at the PCs, and tendrils of strangely colored fire lash out of the runewell, each targeting a different PC in the area. The effects of these tendrils vary according to their color; these ranged Strikes can target anyone in the Eye of Arrogance and accrue multiple attack penalties normally.</p>"
